  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>The latest meeting of the US ‚ÄìChina Strategic and Economic Dialogue (S&amp;ED) was held May 9 and 10 in Washington, DC and the two outcomes papers are out:  The <a href="http://www.state.gov/r/pa/prs/ps/2011/05/162967.htm">Strategic Track</a>, which is essentially political, but also covers climate and energy, and the <a href="http://www.treasury.gov/press-center/press-releases/Pages/tg1170.aspx">Economic Track</a>, which is led by Treasury, but covers a number of trade and investment issues of interest to the energy industry.</p></div>
