  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../expert/edward-cunningham">Edward Cunningham</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Edward_Cunningham_0.jpg" alt="" title="" width="100" height="100" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>Edward Cunningham is an Assistant Professor at Boston University&#8217;s Geography and Environment &amp; Center for Energy and Environmental Studies. His research focuses on the political economy of development and, more specifically, comparative energy governance. He employs surveys and qualitative case studies to examine the relationship between political structure and industrial structure, and the strategies states and firms adopt to manage risk in economic development. His current work assesses the impact of governance decentralization on the environmental sustainability and productivity of energy markets, particularly in China and Indonesia.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-contact-info-value">
                <div class="field-content"><p><a href="mailto:&#101;&#100;&#119;&#97;&#114;&#100;&#95;&#99;&#117;&#110;&#110;&#105;&#110;&#103;&#104;&#97;&#109;&#64;&#104;&#107;&#115;&#46;&#104;&#97;&#114;&#118;&#97;&#114;&#100;&#46;&#101;&#100;&#117;">&#101;&#100;&#119;&#97;&#114;&#100;&#95;&#99;&#117;&#110;&#110;&#105;&#110;&#103;&#104;&#97;&#109;&#64;&#104;&#107;&#115;&#46;&#104;&#97;&#114;&#118;&#97;&#114;&#100;&#46;&#101;&#100;&#117;</a></p>

<p>617-384-8118</p></div>
  </div>
